Assisted students in course selection and career advice, supporting their aspirations for medical entrance exams, while also streamlining communication channels between students and internal teams.

experience.description: Served as a key point of contact for new hires and students, delivering onboarding, orientation, and continuous support. Supported talent acquisition and recruitment activities, from posting job openings to coordinating interviews and onboarding new employees. Assisted in developing and executing onboarding and training programs, fostering a cohesive and motivated team in a fluctuating workload scenario. Supported HR administrative functions such as maintaining employee and student records, processing documentation, and supporting engagement activities in a seasonal environment. Monitored compliance with NEET policies, counseling schedules, and admission guidelines, ensuring that both HR and counseling operations adhered to current standards. Collaborated cross-functionally with teams to ensure effective communication, compliance, and operational efficiency during peak and off-peak seasons. Coordinated recruitment drives, screened candidates, and supported the onboarding of new team members, aligning HR operations with seasonal business needs. Facilitated induction sessions for new employees and students, ensuring clarity on organizational policies, process workflows, and role expectations. Organized and supported career counseling initiatives, including NEET UG & PG counseling sessions, seminars, and awareness programs to assist students with admissions and career planning. Assisted students in course selection and career advice, supporting their aspirations for medical entrance exams, while also streamlining communication channels between students and internal teams.

Assisted students in course selection and career advice, supporting their aspirations for medical entrance exams, while also streamlining communication channels between students and internal teams.

I have over 29 years of experience in operation of sugar industry out of which 10 years as Head Process (Departmental Head) and reporting directly to Unit Head. I even organize a team of Process Personnel for erection and commissioning of new factory. I work in remote villages. I have the ability to adopt easily to the local culture. I have worked 13 years in Karnataka, 11 years in Tamilnadu and 2 years in Orissa. I am fluent in Hindi, Kannada, English and Tamil language. I have done my school and college studies in North India. I have 3 years abroad erection & commissioning experience in Uganda & Sri Lanka.

experience.title: Deputy General Manager Process (Sugar Factory)
experience.description:
1. To Lead and Manage a large team by Co ordinating with different department and section in achieving the desired output.

2. To ensure smooth operation in production from time to time.

3. To Plan, Maintain and Control the activities in production of Sugar

4. To Monitor and Control the sugar losses in Process. Also to check the optimum usage of chemicals in manufacturing of Sugar.

5. To achieve desirable quantity with consistent quality of Sugar.

6.  Accountable for production activities that includes process monitoring, prompt break down service to minimize plant / machinery down time.

7. Accountable for safety in operation.

8. Have done three Projects of complete erection and commissioning of boiling house in sugar industry.

9. To live and work in remote villages.

-Oversee other operations as assigned by the Director

detailed_profile.about: "An ideologue interested in creative solutions" I am an experienced HR professional with strong expertise in Recruitment, HR Operations, Payroll Management, and Employee Counseling. Over the years, I’ve successfully supported organizations in building high-performing teams, streamlining HR processes, and ensuring smooth employee lifecycle management.
